<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe most entertaining outcome is the =
most likely,=E2=80=9D Elon Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0d=
XMvMTM0NzEyNjc5NDE3Mjk0ODQ4Mw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9836fd8a" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 once tweeted</a>, as far as I can tell not about a particular event but as=
 a general life philosophy. In that spirit, let me put out into the world t=
hat the most entertaining outcome of Musk=E2=80=99s deal to buy Twitter Inc=
. is obviously:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Having <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1=
lbG9uLW11c2staGFzLXRocmVlLXdlZWtzLXRvLWNoYW5nZS1oaXMtbWluZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMD=
I0MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1d=
G1fdGVybT0yMjEwMjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B6a7c2ecd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">  agreed</a> to close the deal by 5 p.m. this Friday, Mu=
sk in fact closes the deal by 5 p.m. this Friday, paying $54.20 per share t=
o all of Twitter=E2=80=99s shareholders and taking over the company.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">At 5:01, Joe Biden calls Musk and says=
 =E2=80=9CI am sorry, but we have decided that it is a national security ri=
sk for you to own Twitter,=C2=A0you will have to divest it immediately, thi=
s is an unreviewable and final order.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Musk has to sell the company by noon on Monday, which he does =
at a fire-sale price to =E2=80=A6=C2=A0its previous public shareholders? Hi=
s lenders? Jeff Bezos? Mark Zuckerberg? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwM=
jIvMTAvMTgvMjM0MTA4MTYva2FueWUtcGFybGVyLWFjcXVpc2l0aW9uLWJ1c2luZXNzLWhpc3Rv=
cnktZnJlZS1zcGVlY2gtc3BhbQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8f254ac5" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Kanye=
 West</a>? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2947480=
9.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMT=
AtMDMvZXZlcnlvbmUtd2FudGVkLXRvLWJ1eS10d2l0dGVyLXdpdGgtZWxvbj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxM=
DI0MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1=
dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB4e8f6684" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">  Jason Calacanis=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Crandos=E2=80=9D</a=
>? Lots of good options here.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He b=
uys it for $54.20 per share this week and sells it for like $15 per share n=
ext week, losing tens of billions of dollars.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">Probably he has a really intense weekend of messing around with=
 Twitter before letting it go? Again, many opportunities for antics.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This does not exactly hang together for a numb=
er of reasons, but would it be funny? Yes. Is it the most likely outcome? N=
o. Is it a=C2=A0<em>possible=C2=A0</em>outcome? Not really, no. But everyth=
ing about this deal has skated pretty close to the edge of the possible, so=
 who cares, I am typing it anyway, just in case.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Point 1, it does seem like the deal will cl=
ose this week. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Paula Seligson, Katie Roof and Ed Hammon=
d <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjEvdHdpdHR=
lci1tdXNrLXRhbGtzLXdhcm0tdXAtYXMtYnV5b3V0LWNsb3NpbmctZGVhZGxpbmUtbmVhcnM_Y2=
1waWQ9QkJEMTAyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld=
3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMDI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB3884ebfb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">  reported last week</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both sides=E2=80=99 bankers and lawyers are pr=
eparing paperwork for the buyout to be completed by the Oct. 28 court-issue=
d deadline, the people said, asking not to be identified because the matter=
 is private.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After months of public acrimony and accusation=
s, talks between the two sides have turned cordial and are focused on closi=
ng the transaction rather than litigation, according to one of the people.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Wall Street banks involved, led by Morgan =
Stanley, are also ironing out the steps needed to finalize funding about $1=
3 billion of debt commitments. One of the banks has told its staff to expec=
t a borrowing notice from Musk on Tuesday, said another person familiar wit=
h the matter. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s unclear what led to the breakthro=
ugh between Twitter and Musk. In early October, their talks were stuck over=
 Musk=E2=80=99s statement that his offer was contingent on receiving $13 bi=
llion in debt financing, even though banks were already on the hook to prov=
ide the debt through a commitment letter from April.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another sticking point was that Musk had been =
seeking to reserve his rights to file a fraud lawsuit over his claims the p=
latform=E2=80=99s executives misled him and other investors about the numbe=
r of spam and automated accounts, Bloomberg News reported.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1lbG9uLW11c2st=
aGFzLXRocmVlLXdlZWtzLXRvLWNoYW5nZS1oaXMtbWluZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDI0MjJfTU9ORVl=
TVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMj=
EwMjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6a7c2ecd" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">  talked about this</a> a few weeks ago: Twitter=E2=80=99s lawsuit to=
 force Musk to close was barreling toward trial, even as they were also try=
ing to negotiate a settlement where he closed the deal. But then the=C2=A0j=
udge in the case paused the trial and gave Musk until this Friday to close =
the deal, which made everything much simpler. For one thing, the litigators=
 who were preparing for trial were sidelined, and the deal lawyers responsi=
ble for things like writing the closing documents got to go back to work.=
=C2=A0<em>Of course=C2=A0</em>the talks turned more cordial.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For another thing, those sticking points don=
=E2=80=99t actually matter. =E2=80=9CShould closing be contingent on receiv=
ing the financing=E2=80=9D is an interesting question if you are a Twitter =
lawyer fighting over whether or not to=C2=A0pause the trial, but once the t=
rial is paused and there=E2=80=99s a deadline for closing, the contingency =
is irrelevant: Either he gets funding and closes, or he doesn=E2=80=99t clo=
se (for financing reasons or otherwise) and you go back to court. =E2=80=9C=
Should he reserve his rights to file a fraud lawsuit=E2=80=9D is also compl=
etely irrelevant to the closing: He=E2=80=99ll close the deal by Friday, an=
d then if he really wants to keep suing Twitter=C2=A0he can.<a class=3D"foo=
tnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !importa=
nt; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Point 2, Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Jennifer Jacob=
s and Saleha Mohsin also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjItMTAtMjEvdXMtd2VpZ2hzLXNlY3VyaXR5LXJldmlld3MtZm9yLW11c2stZGVhbHMtaW5=
jbHVkaW5nLXR3aXR0ZXItYnV5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW=
09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ=
249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1c18ac3a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  reported las=
t week</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Biden administration officials are discussing =
whether the US should subject some of Elon Musk=E2=80=99s ventures to natio=
nal security reviews, including the deal for Twitter Inc. and SpaceX=E2=80=
=99s Starlink satellite network, according to people familiar with the matt=
er. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">US officials have grown uncomfortable over Mus=
k=E2=80=99s recent threat to stop supplying the Starlink satellite service =
to Ukraine -- he said it had cost him $80 million so far -- and what they s=
ee as his increasingly Russia-friendly stance following a series of tweets =
that outlined peace proposals favorable to President Vladimir Putin. They a=
re also concerned by his plans to buy Twitter with a group of foreign inves=
tors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The discussions are still at an early stage, t=
he people familiar said on condition of anonymity. Officials in the US gove=
rnment and intelligence community are weighing what tools, if any, are avai=
lable that would allow the federal government to review Musk=E2=80=99s vent=
ures.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possibility is through the law governing t=
he Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States to review Musk=E2=
=80=99s deals and operations for national security risks, they said. =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One element of the $44 billion Twitter deal th=
at could trigger a CFIUS review is the presence of foreign investors in Mus=
k=E2=80=99s consortium. The group includes Prince Alwaleed bin Talal of Sau=
di Arabia, Binance Holdings Ltd. -- a digital-asset exchange founded and ru=
n by a Chinese native -- and Qatar=E2=80=99s sovereign wealth fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The panel operates behind closed doors and rar=
ely confirms when it is conducting reviews. CFIUS also holds the power to r=
eview deals that have already been consummated.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk is a US citizen, so he is probably not su=
bject to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.=
275498/aHR0cHM6Ly9ob21lLnRyZWFzdXJ5Lmdvdi9wb2xpY3ktaXNzdWVzL2ludGVybmF0aW9u=
YWwvdGhlLWNvbW1pdHRlZS1vbi1mb3JlaWduLWludmVzdG1lbnQtaW4tdGhlLXVuaXRlZC1zdGF=
0ZXMtY2ZpdXM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa865c483" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> CFIUS review</a>,<=
a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transp=
arent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>and kicking out his minority co-investors like Prince Alwaleed bin Tala=
l or Binance would not derail the deal. I do not=C2=A0think there=E2=80=99s=
 much of a chance=C2=A0that any US government review will actually block th=
e deal this week, or unwind it in the future. Oh sure I have <em>joked=C2=
=A0</em>about it happening, and about it being Musk=E2=80=99s plan to get o=
ut of the deal; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29=
474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jItMTAtMTIvZGVmaS1kaXNjb3ZlcnMtbmV3LW1hcmtldC1tYW5pcHVsYXRpb25zP2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDEwMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBa678d4e8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  I wrote</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fancier=C2=A0possibility is that he is try=
ing to=C2=A0<em>get American government officials worried</em>, so that the=
y will step in to block the Twitter deal. =E2=80=9CWe can=E2=80=99t let Twi=
tter, the =E2=80=98town square=E2=80=99 of American political discourse, be=
 owned by a guy who might be a Chinese or Russian agent, so we have to bloc=
k the deal,=E2=80=9D people think Musk thinks the government=C2=A0will thin=
k. By winkingly hinting=C2=A0that he might be doing Vladimir Putin=E2=80=99=
s bidding, the theory goes, Musk will force the US government to=C2=A0block=
 his acquisition of Twitter. Which would get him out of it, which is =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0perhaps =E2=80=94=C2=A0what he wants.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t really buy this =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0I don=E2=80=99t think that the US government has much of a mechanism to =
block the deal at this point, and I think it would be too controversial for=
 anyone to touch =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it is a=C2=A0<em>funny=C2=A0</em>theory=
 so I am passing it along.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk has also joked about it: Last week <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6=
