00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> fi=
re everyone</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk told prospective investors in his de=
al to buy the company that he planned to get rid of nearly 75 percent of Tw=
itter=E2=80=99s 7,500 workers, whittling the company down to a skeleton sta=
ff of just over 2,000. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The impact of such layoffs would likely be imm=
ediately felt by millions of users, said Edwin Chen, a data scientist forme=
rly in charge of Twitter=E2=80=99s spam and health metrics and now CEO of t=
he content-moderation start-up Surge AI. He said that while he believed Twi=
tter was overstaffed, the cuts Musk proposed were =E2=80=9Cunimaginable=E2=
=80=9D and would put Twitter=E2=80=99s users at risk of hacks and exposure =
to offensive material such as child pornography.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt would be a cascading effect,=E2=80=
=9D he said, =E2=80=9Cwhere you=E2=80=99d have services going down and the =
people remaining not having the institutional knowledge to get them back up=
, and being completely demoralized and wanting to leave themselves.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As far as I can tell Musk=E2=80=99s basic cont=
ent plans for Twitter are (1) less moderation and (2)=C2=A0less spam, and w=
hile those goals do not <em>logically</em> conflict with=C2=A0each other, t=
here is an obvious practical tension. Detecting and blocking violent, abusi=
ve, racist, anti-Semitic, etc. content is not the <em>same=C2=A0</em>activi=
ty as detecting and blocking spam, but it does seem like they=E2=80=99d use=
 overlapping skills and processes. If your philosophical goal is to stop mo=
derating content, then that works well with your financial goal of firing e=
veryone. But if you want to block spam, you need people to block the spam.<=
/p>
