<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">UBS v. UBS</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are the chief executive officer of an i=
nvestment bank, it is tempting to think that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjAvbW9yZ2FuLXN0YW5sZXktbG9zdC1zb21lLWh=
hcmQtZHJpdmVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdX=
RtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzd=
HVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4670546d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> your bank is a tech com=
pany</a>. =E2=80=9CWe provide technology tools to our clients to do stuff w=
ith money,=E2=80=9D is the basic pitch, with the technology including both =
(1) financial technology (derivatives, structured notes, trade execution, f=
unds, etc.) and (2) increasingly,=C2=A0computer technology (apps, smart rou=
ters, robo-advisers, a website where you can check your account balance, et=
c.). Becoming=C2=A0a tech company is a good development for a bank:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Doing tech stuff is less capital-inte=
nsive than doing traditional finance stuff. Traditionally banks use their b=
alance sheets to intermediate trades=C2=A0between customers; writing a comp=
uter program to intermediate those trades uses less capital.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Doing tech stuff is less=C2=A0<em>people-</em>in=
tensive than doing traditional finance stuff. Banks are famously businesses=
 where =E2=80=9Cthe assets walk out the door every evening,=E2=80=9D becaus=
e the most important assets are the people, who have the market knowledge a=
nd client relationships that make up the value of the bank.=C2=A0This gives=
 them=C2=A0leverage to demand perks and bonuses and to jump ship to competi=
tors. Whereas if you build an app, it<em> doesn=E2=80=99t</em> walk out the=
 door every evening. The market knowledge and client relationships live on =
your servers.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Tech companies just =
seem like good businesses: It is easier to scale an app than a relationship=
 business (you don=E2=80=99t have to hire and train thousands of copies of =
the app), it creates more stable revenue (the trading platform you offer to=
 clients is less likely to lose a billion dollars on a trade than your trad=
ing=C2=A0<em>desk=C2=A0</em>is), it gets valued more highly by investors, e=
tc.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Point 2 has a clear appeal to a bank=E2=80=99s=
=C2=A0<em>CEO</em>, but is less appealing to the people one or two levels b=
eneath her. For a CEO, it is good to depend less on the personal skills of =
temperamental senior bankers. For those senior bankers, it is bad.=C2=A0</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29474809.275498/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlYXR1cmVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjMvdWJzLXMtcml2YWxyeS1hdC10aGUtdmVyeS1=
0b3AtaXMtcGxheWluZy1vdXQtdW5kZXJncm91bmQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRk=
YmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMDI0J=
nV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfee15a60" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 Marion Halftermeyer and Myriam Balezou report</a> on conflict between Ralp=
h Hamers, the chief executive officer of UBS Group AG, who understandably w=
ants UBS to be a tech company, and Iqbal Khan, the head of UBS=E2=80=99s we=
alth business, who understandably does not:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Dutch-born CEO =E2=80=94 widely viewed as =
a surprise pick when he joined two years ago =E2=80=94 wants to harness aut=
omated tools, streamline the byzantine executive ranks and improve the comp=
any=E2=80=99s standing in the US, where UBS is eclipsed by local rivals. Me=
eting those goals requires the embrace of lower-margin robo advice via algo=
rithms and mobile apps, not an easy ask of a breed of bankers accustomed to=
 providing a personal touch. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But those attuned to Khan=E2=80=99s more tradi=
tional way of doing business are concerned about diluting a cherished brand=
 built over 160 years around banking for the rich. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ever the consummate networker, Khan likes to h=
ost gatherings at his lake-view villa in Zurich, where he mingles with infl=
uential business leaders, clients and shareholders.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He makes regular use of the corporate jet to c=
risscross the globe and visit customers. As Khan said at a conference last =
month, =E2=80=9Ceverything we do starts with clients.=E2=80=9D But how exac=
tly that connection is created is where the fault line runs. On one trip to=
 the US this month, Khan encouraged employees in Los Angeles to build advis=
ory relationships "not with machines, but people," according to one person =
who attended the gathering.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hamers, on the other hand, has said clients te=
ll him that UBS has great products and the best advice, but that the bank m=
ust improve on its digital delivery.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The app doesn=E2=80=99t fly on the corporate j=
et, the app doesn=E2=80=99t host gatherings at a villa, the app doesn=E2=80=
=99t have the personal touch of a talented senior banker. But the app does =
scale, and the app is very unlikely to cultivate support among UBS=E2=80=99=
s board and shareholders to try to win a power struggle with the CEO.=C2=A0=
</p>
